<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">'</span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style=""><div style="margin: 0px;"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><div style="">Please see below some updates from school for your information.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><b>Air Quality&nbsp;</b></div><div style="">As you will be aware we actively monitor the air quality around the campus and have noticed that the air quality has started to deteriorate.&nbsp; The trend is that the air quality is at its worst at 6.00am but it seems to improve as the day goes on.&nbsp; So far we have not had to cancel any outdoor play, however, we did have to stop the early morning swimming training today.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">To keep you informed from the school side please be aware that we are currently working on the following;</div><div style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style="">- Daily monitoring of numbers as per the policy (attached for reference)</div><div style="">- Ensuring all of the air purifiers in school are switched on, fitted with new filters and working well</div><div style="">- We have invested in a further 30 air purifiers to put around the campus, these will be delivered this week.&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div style="">- We will shortly install a iPad near the parent communications board that shows a live link to the air quality.&nbsp; All senior members of staff and PE staff already have an app which tells them real time readings from around the campus.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style="">- We will publish our air quality on the Air Visual Website (this may take a few weeks) - please see this <a href="https://www.airvisual.com/air-quality-map?lat=16.856831&amp;lng=96.146523&amp;zoomLevel=15">link</a> for more information</div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><b>Pedestrian Access&nbsp;</b></div><div style="">As part of our ongoing efforts to ensure a safe and secure campus, we have been looking at pedestrian access to the school.&nbsp; After some consideration we will be looking to install a new gate that will be in operation after the half term break.&nbsp; The new gate will be located just past the main entrance for cars.&nbsp; Pedestrians will be able to walk through the gate and will gain access to the school through the small carpark and into the side entrance.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><b>Uniform</b></div><div style="">As previously communicated all students should now be wearing the new uniform (Apart from Year 11) The old BSF garments should no longer be worn in school.&nbsp; We have now seen sample of the improvements we requested to the new uniform and have placed an order to update our stock.&nbsp; If your child is one of the few who does not have a new uniform they may wear the new PE uniform until the new stock arrives.&nbsp; (We will update you when the new stock arrives)<b>&nbsp;</b></div><div style=""><b><br></b></div><div style="">Finally a big thank you to everyone for working with us on the new morning drop off routine.&nbsp; We are working on improvements and will continue to refine the process in the coming weeks.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Kind regards&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Mark&nbsp;</div><div style=""><br></div><div style="">Mark Johnson&nbsp;</div><div style="">Business Director&nbsp;</div></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
